          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thin deuterated polyethylene (CD2) n foils were",
                "deployed: 242 mu- g/cm2 for 126,128Sn beams and 139",
                "mu-g/cm2 for 124Sn."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Super Oak Ridge Rutgers University Barrel",
                "Array (SuperORRUBA) , deployed to detect charged",
                "particles, consisted of ten 1000 mu-m thick silicon",
                "detectors covering 55deg - 89deg in the laboratory",
                "and two covering 92deg - 125deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In this experiment spectroscopic information for the",
                "f- and p-wave single-neutron states populated by the",
                " (d,p) reaction on neutron-rich tin isotopes were",
                "determined. The excitation energies, spins, parities,",
                "and spectroscopic information determined",
                "experimentally were used for direct- semidirect",
                "calculations of (n,g) reaction cross using the code",
                "CUPIDO. Both real and imaginary parts of the incident",
                "channel were calculated using the Koning-Delaroche",
                "potential. The reaction (d,p) has been validated as",
                "a surrogate for neutron capture."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
